INFORMATIONALAccessibility1920x1080

Missing level-one heading (H1) on page

The accessibility audit reports: "Page does not contain a level-one heading. Add at least one H1 (or role=heading aria-level=1)." The visible hero area contains prominent branding and messaging (e.g., the SVG/hero text 'Win-Win Loyalty Platform' and 'Cashback for Users, Retention for Business') but these are rendered as SVGs/divs rather than a semantic H1 element. A top-level H1 is required to provide a primary landmark for screen reader users and to improve document outline and navigation.

MEDIUMPerformance1920x1080

Serve large screenshot images in next‑gen formats (WebP/AVIF)

Two large screenshot images used on the page are currently GIFs (examples: /screenshots/business-page-demo-2-light.gif and /screenshots/business-page-demo-2-dark.gif). Each GIF is ~3.78 MB with estimated potential savings of ~1,134,000 bytes per image if converted to WebP or AVIF. Serving these as modern compressed formats reduces network payload, improves load times, and reduces data usage for visitors.

MEDIUMPerformance1920x1080

Serve large hero images in next‑gen formats (convert GIFs to WebP/AVIF)

The audit found two large images used on the page currently served as GIFs (example sources: https://byteback.pro/screenshots/business-page-demo-1-light.gif and https://byteback.pro/screenshots/business-page-demo-1-dark.gif).
